reviews.text: Great food, great staff, and lovely intimate atmosphere.

delicious breakfast 
nice atmosphere
Well cooked, interesting food in pleasant surroundings.
Nice view in the temple and we are fortunate to witness local wedding taking place over there
A must visit place. Love the artistic design
Beautiful temple in the heart of medan.

Sri Mariamman Temple is medan's oldest Hindu tempel. This temple was built in 1884 for the worship of Goddess mariammam.The temple is situated in the area known as kampuang madrass or Medan's littel India. This temple is also devoted to the Hindu Gods ganesha and mrurgan. children of mariamman. The Gate is decorated bygopuram, namely storey tower which can usually be found at the gate of the Hindus temples in south  India. The temple is a meeting point for worshippers during Thaipusam and Deevapali festivals
The location near Sun Plaza shopping Mall and food corner, but the traffic is crowded.

An excellent museum for those who interested for Product Design. It's basically a showcase of Red Dot Award-Winning products. A lot of products to interact with to show you how good the products that win the Red Dot Design Awards.

Great museum of you like design of all kinds. This museum is a collections of all products that have won the Red Dot Design awards. It is located on the grounds of the Ruhr-museum. Very interesting old industrial building. The collection is located over multiple floors and the upper floors have some amazing views towards the lower positioned collection.
Wonderful curated collection of design classics voted for by the Red Dot Commitee.
It’s a very small museum. Just a bunch of new technology and decoration things. Nothing to see here
was here 20 years ago. great to revisit again.

If you are looking for somewhere inexpensive to have some lunch then come here as you have plenty to choose from. At this centre you cam buy almost anything from pork to chicken and everything in between and it will just cost under S$10 For a nice meal.
We have pork and duck meat with a pork soup and it was delicious. If you want to try something different then go for the black skin chicken. For drinks you can get anything from water to tea or coffee.
I had so much fun that hippies are so cool I smoke some of the best weed for the best price

A great space and part of Berkeley's story, student accommodation not sure? A refuge and a place of reflection for Berkeley siders, keep People's Park as it is, a moving story and inportant history that should be preserved and improved.

Peoples Park is a precious green space. I play live acoustic music at Peoples Park whenever I get a chance, guitar songs, jazz, funk, folk, rock, samba, bossa nova, percussion... I have old friends there and did community gardening there for five years, growing 13 foot tall corn and green beans, and all kinds of stuff. The trees and plants there are good old friends too. I've heard lots of great bands on the Free Speech Stage, summer concerts, the Berkeley World Music series, drum jams, dancing. Its very interesting, I've learned a lot there, talking to people, about history, people, culture, plants, gardening.

I have always loved this old park.
Sad it is always under attack and it is purposely kept decrepit by the University to justify building on it.
Guess everyone will use Williard Park should the unelected have their way.

Loved all of the accompanying dishes so you can create your own flavor combos. We got there just in time, around 6:30 before the mobs of people started to arrive around 7. The service was terrific, fast, warm smiles and the staff all had a collective effort. Be sure to say hi to the owner/host, he was the nicest guy and you can tell he took pride in his restaurant. We’ll definitely be back, but next time we’re trying the bbq table :) 

Also - be sure to get the chicken dumplings to start

It was good but I wouldn't say that it was stellar and I would come back. The food was average and the place is definitely historic. They need to up their game given there are many other fantastic korean good food options in Austin now. The place is a little hard to find as it is tucked away near a small Chinese Zen garden. The service was okay and took a while. We requested a few things but didn't get it on time. We had to ask the waiter multiple times. The interior was a little dim and bland. The tofu soup was really great though, not so sure about the cold noodles. It is worth a one time try but I can't fully recommend it as a too option, there are a lot other better ones.
We got Korean BBQ combo and everything was amazing! Great atmosphere, very helpful staff. Loved it!!
Have been coming here for ten years plus. Never a bad experience! Great atmosphere, and wonderful people.

Always great. They have cleaned, updated and renovated the place. They also performed a menu update after the previous owner, who was also the sushi chef, retired. No more sushi is a bummer. Also, my favorite dish consisting of stir fried baby octopus is gone. I was initially sad that my favorite dish was gone but it forced me to try something new and I was not let down! They were busy for lunch and all the diners seemed content. I will always come back.
Very good Boston Chinatown seafood and Cantonese food. Ambiance is typically dumpy Chinatown. Food makes up for it. Lots of live seafood in tanks that you can order up.

There are a lot of good restaurants in Boston's Chinatown and this place too is pretty good. It's not great though.  The rice was a little old and the dumplings were overly chewy.  Other than that,  food was delicious. The soup was really spicy so be aware!
This place is great and the employees are very friendly. Cool spot for sure!
The food was okay. The service felt forced and rushed. Where we were seated was not clean.
I've only had takeout lunches from New Jumbo and the food is copious, decent, and cheap. Only about $5 for a lunch including rice, soup, and an appetizer.

Food is of very good quality. The 3 star review is for the attitude of people and the service provided.

"Whats special here" was our question, to which he says "Nothing". When we said we are coming from another part of the country and we need to try local cuisine. 

Either the waiter was in bad mood or thats how they behave. Took their sweet time to serve food. Sometimes, last arrived people received food before the ones who arrived earlier.

One of the best restaurant in town. Delicious and healthy food. Vast variety in menu. Best for South Indian food, sizzlers and continental. A complete family restaurant and a good place to hangout with friends. Love this place. Thumbs up.

Very nice food.....lovely place...Easy to locate with or without Google maps...lacks parking facility but otherwise it's best. Food is very yummy with the choice of normal and Jain meals, specially the mocktails they are just best. Responsible staff with good service....food served within the time they say..good sitting facilities.

Good option for dinning at Allahabad. Little bit costly according to quality. Larg group of 40-50 can be accommodated. North Indian and South Indian dishes are quite good. Quite pleasant and beautiful ambience... Very good service and very active staff... Overall had a very pleasant and praise worthy experience...👌👌👌

Sagar Ratna pure veg restaurant is a renowned restaurant in Allahabad which is very famous for its vegetarian dishes and Continental dishes..... I have tried some of the best dosas cutlets and their veg starters parking maybe an issue because they don't have their own personal parking space ..... the staffs are highly cooperative and you can even talk to chef in case you want to change the taste of your dishes.

..
Shopping mall and Hotel ( Novotel).  Very convenient, location, good restaurants also. Three is a train(subway) station, so you can easy get to airport o any other part of peninsula or island.

What a fantastic little hidden gem. The store is beautiful and the experience provided by the sales staff especially, Lana was fantastic. From the moment I walked in she was very welcoming and attentive. Her knowledge of the products and her advice was exceptional. She made the process of finding a style and colour to suit me very easy. She has wonderful customer service and I would highly recommend the store and Lana for the purchase of your next special gown.

Far from being an outlet.
Prices are high, old fashion, old collections. 
Don't waste your time here.
Great shopping mall to enjoy the restaurants around here and one thing to note is that there's a hotel here as well. This place is a good stopover since it is near the MTR (subway) station as well.

A seriously good collection of discounted brand names although I've come to realize these discounts are now nowhere near as good as they were 2-3 years ago. Who's kidding who? The influx of mainland Chinese on buying trips has caused a disproportionate rise in store prices. This is no longer a shoppers paradise like it was in 2013-2017!! I've bought may items here over the years from many different stores but I've found princess today are not as discounted from outside prices as the stores say they are. Greed has crept back in at Citygate. Local code shops and restaurants are still ok.
Love the place, great food. I recommend the noodles with peanut sauce for sure and all dim sum was great overall.

It's too busy... They won't give you the attention the focus your looking for. 

I was disappointed.
Loved the Xiao long bao (plain pork) ! Very delicious, especially the chocolate ones, which I highly recommend!

The place that could never be wrong when you're in a delicacy hunger. Their services staff are at least 4 levels/types and the food is typical Cantonese cuisine. The crab one is a can't miss, seasonal seafood is a nice surprise.

Great place for Chinese dumplings and other dishes. The restaurant is on the expensive side as for Chinese pricing but it is well worth it. The management speaks English also so it is easy to communicate. Menu's are clear and with pictures so you can also pick and choose what to eat. Great for both locals and foreigners.

Dinner was blah and bland. Overpriced. Waiter was awesome. Dessert was superb - lemon blueberry cake!  Previous visit for lunch was yummy and great value for the food.  Great lunch spot.  Spouse prefers the bar menu.

Can't beat half priced wine bottles on a Friday night. They had a live band as well, which was fun. Server was very friendly. I ordered the fish sandwich for my meal and it was quite good. My parents enjoyed their prime rib sandwich and french onion soup as well.

I’ll preface this by saying that this is one of the nicest restaurants in Binghamton. 

With that said, I think it’s a bit overrated and grossly overpriced. The prices are similar to those you’d find in a Manhattan steakhouse which is a bit ridiculous, as the quality is nowhere near the same. It’s a bit odd that it’s sort of a combination of a sports bar and a high class restaurant. My steak was over cooked and tough, and the entrees were mediocre at best and certainly not worth the price. It’s a good place for one night out but not much more.

Food is wildly overpriced and overrated; their reputation for excellence is exaggerated by sentimental locals. That being said, it is decent for Binghamton, but still overpriced. Good service also extends only to locals/regulars, so if you're from out of town I'd suggest going elsewhere.
One of the best restaurants in Binghamton. Sit upstairs if you prefer a quieter atmosphere... Downstairs was quite loud.

This recent trip is our family’s second stay at Shangrila Bangkok. The first was awesome, which brought us back for our second. This stay has been comfortable and enjoying for my children, as well as my parents. Friendly and helpful staff at the lobby on our arrival. My 6 year old girl vomited after our taxi ride from the airport. A few female young staff were extremely helpful, quickly handing us towels and helped consoling my girl, and later offered her a drink. These staff were so fast and so helpful! We felt very warm at heart!!! Our balcony rooms were wonderful. And I must highly recommend the breakfast at next2. Superb variety, great food and very attentive service! We will definitely come back!

Thank you for the colleague who did the check in. Even our room booking was under staff rate, she was patient to introduce and solve our problem which was treating us as guest. Very helpful and kind.
Also, the Chi spa was excellent. I went to Thailand and tried different spa for many times. The therapist-Honey in Chi spa was even the best. Her warm smile made me felt welcomed at the beginning and the massage made me felt worth to pay. Thank you for the relaxing experience she gave to me.

This place has been around for a while now, and it's well-known among the locals - for good reason! It's a superb hotel, and the staff members are excellent. Our company reserved the conference hall for a half day and evening for a full company meeting, and everything went really well. The Chinese dinner they served was excellent! (Peking duck - very, very good.)

Really, there are no complaints about this place. It's an added bonus that the hotel is sitting right next to the Chaophraya River, and you can get great views from the hotel bar or even the pool deck.

Would be a great getaway place.

I would have loved to give it a 5 star because of its location and ambience but reducing a star for complexity of navigating between meeting rooms and Building wings. You can't help being lost. Having said that, staff are very helpful and show you the way and you reach your destination walking really long!

The staff were kind, and the food in the lounge was delicious.
Only thing to be improved is cleanliness of the table in the lounge. I could see the traces of the cups left in many places and a little bit sticky when I am touching on surface of the table. It seems they have not wiped the table clean after the customer left.

And the communication skill/ background information about hotel facility should be more improved. We asked if we could borrow ping-pong racket /ball to play table tennis near swimming pool (Depending on each hotel policy, we used to borrow the racket and ball before) however, the staff in Krungthep lobby told us that we have to purchase the racket and ball in Robinson shopping mall whereas we found that racket and ball were equipped beside on the table while taking a walk later.

Очень впечатляет особенно ночью.
 Армянская церковь, 1742 - 1762 гг. В стиле барокко, сооружен на месте деревянного, основанного в 1665 г. Первые известные реставрации и перестройки произведены в 1811 и 1829 гг. Во время пожара 1868 г. сооружение было частично разрушено.
        После неудачной реставрации, проведенной в 1868 г. по проекту инж. Треле, здание значительно изменило свой внешний облик. Две круглые башни, фланкирующие главный фасад, стали значительно ниже, а их завершения - шлемы барочного силуэта - заменены обычными колоколо образными куполами. Иным по конфигурации стал фронтон, исчезла небольшая башня, венчавшая крышу.
       Интерьер храма украшен скульптурами(Матвей Полейовский) и фресками(Ян Солецкий).

Гарна церква з цікавим фасадом. Можливо б потребувала вона трішки реконструкції. В середині також красиво, але по стилю зовнішній вигляд не співпадає із стилістикою інтер'єру. Хоч вона прихована за іншими будинками, але завдяки яскравому пофарбуванню, помітна здалека.
Дуже гарна - Дуже подобається
Гарно виглядає
Православная церковь.

You'd be hard pressed to find better food in Atlanta.  Farm to table fresh, inventive creations from the chef, service polished to near perfection, and a lovely setting make it an excellent destination.   Yet, there's something that feels formulaic--the spontaneity and uniqueness of dining here is lessened from the Bacchanalia of old.  Still, it's very worthwhile for that special occasion or for any evening when you're okay to drop a few pennies.

Went to Bacchanalia a few years ago with my wife and it was really good, but we felt like it feel a little short of all the hype. Fast forward to this month, we went again to try out their new home on the Westside, and we were blown away. I sincerely could not have asked for a better experience or food. The service was impeccable. The food was perfectly portioned and prepared. I had a hard time choosing what to order because everything on the menu, within each course, sounded so good. I'll be back very soon and highly recommend Bacchanalia. It was once the restaurant in Atlanta that received top honors every year, and if they haven't regained that title, they certainly deserve to.

Amazing service and attention to detail. The staff was incredibly considerate and made every aspect of the evening enjoyable. Unquestionably the food was amazing and the atmosphere was perfect. I couldn't recommend a restaurant more.

Bacchanalia was very professional and tasty, but lacked a few things necessary for me to rate 5 stars at this price point. The location is great and avoids local road traffic in the area. I also really appreciated the self-parking. The dining room wasn't too loud and had a neat feeling, but there were a few quirks (e.g. the tables that lock you in to the bench seats and lights dimmed every time the bar dishwasher turned on). All the food was very tasty, but didn't quite blow our minds the way I would expect for a $250+ dinner. The only true disappointment was the beer list. I ordered the best IPA on tap (Wicked Weed Freak of Nature), but was informed it had already tapped out...at 6:15pm. There wasn't anything else comparable to replace it.  I wish restaurants (especially at this level) would update their beer list to reflect what is actually available.

The service was top-notch, but lacked warmth. We had everything we needed (and never thought about water), but there was no personal connection. Maybe that's their operating model?

Overall, we felt like One Midtown Kitchen (now closed) and Local Three offer more creative/impressive dishes and friendlier service at a better price point compared to Bacchanalia.

Absolutely amazing restaurant! The staff is responsive and professional and my glass was never empty. The food was fabulous and we’ll portioned. I recommend business casual attire with a jacket no tie.
Very Good restaurant and awesome food and aumbience..
Posch.  Excellent wine

I hope I am the first and the last one to rate this place. 

At first, we were asked to seat in the corner of the restaurant with no one coming to attend us for next ten minutes. 

Our waiter for the day - Prasanna was not at all the knowledgable on the menu. He didn't even bring the Drinks menu to us in the first place. After we insisted, he got us just one menu, seeing there are two people on the table.

We wanted to have Old Fashioned and Prasanna had no idea what that drink was. We were later informed that the restaurant ran out of bitter. How can a hotel like Taj run out of bitter ?  We settled for Kingfisher Beer. 

The dinner started off in a very disappointing way when we were served some tasteless Anitpasti that can only be compared to Corn Fluid. The Main Course tasted equally bad.

For the main course, I ordered a Spaghetti and I made pretty clear that I my pasta needs to be a Spaghetti but I was served Linguine. Again, there was no communication in terms of how our food and our experience was. Moreover, our waiter got us one plate and kept the other guest waiting for next ten minutes. In a restaurant, you always get two plates together. That's restaurant 101. 

This was very disappointing experience. And, I was charged Rs 3600 for this experience. We left the food on the plate and walked away and no one even enquired about that. 

If you still wanna go to this place. Be my guest.

My partner and me went there on a Saturday night for a special celebration. It's being advertised as having 8 rooms but none of them are connected to each other. Each room require a new entry fee (beware). We chose the main room. It was surprisingly small though its the biggest in size among the 8 rooms. The place is pretty much dead before 1am. It was never packed after 1pm. If you do not want to party with people around the age of 20, then this is not your club to go. As for the music, it was terrific compared to other clubs I been to around the world. In a nutshell, there was no flow to the music. Dance floor was small and stuffy hot. Overall, the experience was very poor. Very curious to know whether or not did Zouk paid to get into top 100 clubs? For future go-ers, thinking 10 times before deciding to go or not.

It is a Worst club in KL. Do not recommend going.  Rude service, just because they think they are the best in town.  

Trying to rip tourist off.  Stay away. There are far more better clubs that has a better vibe and friendly service.  Ladies night, was a 3 to 1 guy/girl.  Figure that out.

And you have to pay for parking as well.

I DON’t recommend it.

Was here for ladies night on a Wednesday. Was a little disappointed that only Velvet was opened that evening (Thursdays they have 2 rooms, and Fridays/Saturdays all rooms). It was also really empty until midnight, like, 5 guests in the entire club before that kind of empty. Because of work the next morning, we had to leave early, but from the looks of it, wasn't supposed to expect much in any case. Perhaps more a weekend spot, unlike the Zouk in Singapore where it's always bustling. Also - this place allows cigarettes, so it can be quite an annoying experience for some.
Best For chilling on weekends specially saturday night 😉 Entry ticket is just 50RM in which you can buy a drink too. Beer or Soft drink of your choice.
Awesome place and comfortable. It's getting crowded after 12. So, dont try it before.
